image.altText: A Brisbane Lions player runs away from goal roaring in celebration while pointing his finger.

items.synopsis: Brisbane and Port Adelaide have an eye on a home prelim as they meet in a blockbuster qualifying final at the Gabba. Follow the action in our live blog.

title.children: Lions and Power go goal for goal in electric qualifying final shootout

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Electric stuff in that quarter. Port Adelaide broke the game open in the middle of that second quarter, and for a moment you wondered if the Lions had the speed to match them. They most certainly do. Brisbane took control back around the stoppages turned it into a scoreboard advantage by half-time. But this is a proper arm wrestle, very even across the ground. Port Adelaide's poor goalkicking is really the only difference at this point. Have the Power wasted their brightest moments of the game? Or can they sustain their good play and overwhelm the hosts? Plenty to play for out there in the second half.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Half-time: Lions lead it by 16 points

children.content: Port Adelaide broke the game open in the middle of that second quarter, and for a moment you wondered if the Lions had the speed to match them.
They most certainly do. Brisbane took control back around the stoppages turned it into a scoreboard advantage by half-time.
But this is a proper arm wrestle, very even across the ground. Port Adelaide's poor goalkicking is really the only difference at this point.
Have the Power wasted their brightest moments of the game? Or can they sustain their good play and overwhelm the hosts? Plenty to play for out there in the second half.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: So the Lions take the early lead, but it's pretty close to a stalemate in terms of general play. Both teams having a bit their own way, but both with some things to work on. Chiefly for Port, they've got to start taking their chances. Bad misses to Marshall and Lycett are really the difference in this game so far. Too close to call after the opening term. Fun to watch though.

Too close to call after the opening term. Fun to watch though.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Brandon Smith bent the Sharks back, Terrell May skipped across the middle of the park and created an overlap, with Sam Walker summing it up perfectly with a long ball to Joey Manu, who I think is playing on the wing now. And Walker converts from out wide to tie the scores at 6 to start the second half.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Sam Walker puts Joey Manu over for the Roosters!

children.content: Brandon Smith bent the Sharks back, Terrell May skipped across the middle of the park and created an overlap, with Sam Walker summing it up perfectly with a long ball to Joey Manu, who I think is playing on the wing now.
And Walker converts from out wide to tie the scores at 6 to start the second half.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Both teams are playing with the desperation you'd expect from a sudden-death final, but it's making for a really sloppy affair. The Sharks and Roosters crossed multiple times, but the attack is just out of rhythm for both sides and there are a lot of silly mistakes sneaking into their games.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: HALF-TIME: The Sharks lead the Roosters 6-0
